caption: The vegicurry is incredible! I got mild spice because I feel like lots of spice can overpower subtler flavors, and this may have been the most delicious curry I've ever had - really complex and delicious flavor profile!
Best prime rib in Waikiki unfortunately only available on Sunday. Comes with a very tasty cream corn, horseradish, and choice of rice or French fries. The French fries are a must try.
Friendly staff, excellent food! Got the shrimp curry it was great!
Just Ok.  Everywhere else had a line so I tried to spot it had a pretty good shrimp very very garlicky though
the food is DELICIOUS! The customer service is also amazing. I will definitely come here again next time I visit Honolulu
Great food. Just wish there was more veggie options. They have two veggie dishes and they are essentially the same but use a different base. Why not add tofu or seitan?
Not bad garlic shrimp, but the shrimp is definitely not cooked in the garlic sauce. So there isn't a lot of cohesion in the dish.

Ebinomi is the best!!!! All their food is so delicious and the people always nice and friendly, i just love it! I conserve this restaurant in a special place in my heart, when i went to hawaii this was the first place that i ate the famous and traditional hawaiian garlic shrimp and i fell in love with it and then when it was time to go back home this was the last garlic shrimp i ate too , so grateful  i got to taste it from this place💞 definitely when I visit Honolulu (Waikiki) again this will be my first stop and last stop to keep it as a personal tradition💞💞🥰

I don’t want to leave a bad review however the beef stew was Not good at all and I could not finish it. It seems the beef and the soup was cooked separately and it only had the sour tomato soup flavor overall. Also the rice was mush and I was able to eat 1/4 of the offer. I don’t recommend beef stew.

This place has incredible food and we just found out about the hidden gem. We normally go to north shore for a good shrimp meal but will now eat here right in Waikiki. We ordered the garlic shrimp single meal and split it for 2. Stuart took our order. He was friendly, food was fast, and very filling. 5 stars all the way around

Overall, less than thrilled with this dish. Simply is over cooke garlic in butter, with (7) shrimps. By no means is this unique to the North Shore way of preparing shrimp. They Simply use this for marketing purposes.  I’d suggest looking else where, there are some real gems in this neck of Waikiki.
A must visit place in Waikiki, Honolulu. Amazing taste. Totally worth the money. Great service 👍👍👍
Great garlic shrimp and Sophia was very helpful and knowledgeable about the whole menu.  My go-to place!

My wife and I couldn't get enough of the friendly staff and delicious food at EbiNomi! This quickly became our go-to spot in Waikiki. A hidden gem located just off the main strip, we stumbled across the small storefront (large patio space right outside) our first night in town. Everything was delicious but we especially liked the Thai curry shrimp and potato shrimp. This place is a must, and preferred it to the long lines and (over)hyped Marukame Udon next door. Show EbiNomi some love
Delicious and not too expensive.

Came by this place while looking for something to eat, it’s small and hidden behind another major restaurant. The menu is limited so I was able to try three of the meals and they were all delicious.  The food was prepared for us quickly with good customer service. I was staying close so I was able to eat the food warm and it didn’t disappoint. You definitely have to try the beef stew, it has to be one of the best dishes I had while visiting Hawaii.
Best garlic shrimps in Hawaii! Love its curry which is unique in Oahu. The a la king chicken is super yummy!

Great new take out, order at counter restaurant Located behind the Ramen shop on Kuhio that always has a crazy line.  I ordered the Ebi Curry spicy.  It was delicious.  Generous portion of shrimp and 2 scoops of rice that all tasted extremely fresh.  The curry was flavorful and spicy but not too much that it takes away your sense of taste. They also have  garlic shrimp, a la king (cream), Hungarian beef stew and a ebi cocktail a la Mexican ceviche style.  The gentleman working the counter is friendly and no pressure to order.  Food speaks for itself.  Clean, fresh look and extremely covid conscious.  Tables outside to sit. Highly recommend.

They’re open and very covid safe. There’s a couple tables outside you can sit at. I’ve been here twice and got the chicken curry. I absolutely LOVE curry and this is in my top 5 best. It’s so good and fresh plus they know how to make it spicy which seems to be rare these days. Stewart is very friendly and great to talk to. And the girl that normally works there (she may be a pro surfer??) is also really cool and friendly. I’ll be coming back here every time I’m in town!
Delicious food, friendly service. Had their garlic shrimp.

Great service and yummy food.   They were out of ceviche but the beef stew was enough to feed two of us.  High quality ingredient.     Make sure to order via their website - or call in for #pickup.  Extremely covid safe.   We will be back for more shrimp dishes.   Support local small businesses.
Small unassuming place but their food is great!
We tried Ebikahuku and it's really tasty!

We kept seeing advertising on the news and Instagram showing beautiful pictures of the meals. We decided to take a short drive into Waikiki, The Garlic Shrimp over rice reminded me of the food found on the North shore at the shrimp trucks. That butter and garlic sauce over everything.  We also tried the Curry Shrimp, we ordered the mild sauce level. That was good too. I think there are about 8 pieces of shrimp per dinner. We ended up not finishing it all.  I would suggest maybe getting a salad to add more to the meal. Support local business.
Great little cafe with the delicious and fresh prawns. Reasonable prices for Waikiki area. Definitely recommend.
I eat all kinds of curry and this is among the best curry places I tried. If you like spicy food, you’ll love it. Rice is also very good and nicely cooked.

Omg!!!! This restaurant is a must for a good flavorful meal.. its hidden behind a popular restaurant but omg what a gem.. I got the Hungarian beef stew and soooo good.. definetly a must try.. also the cury has sooo much flavor its amazing I will for sure return here on my next trip to waikiki.
Great food!
Pretty good value, give this place a try if your in the area! I liked the Stew & Veggie curry as a healthier option. They do DoorDash delivery too!

Heard about this new place from friends thought to give it a try.  A bit difficult to find it is not on the main street but in a courtyard behind Marukame Udon.  But quite a gem this is.  My wife had the butter garlic shrimps they call the EbiKahuku and she loved it – no shells not needing to get your fingers greasy.  And the shrimps were not overcooked like some of the previous experience we had on the Northshore.  I had a taste and this is definitely a cut above.  The shrimps are also larger.  I felt like something “beefy” but I am reading mixed reviews here.  But I thought what the hell and gave it a try.  Well I LOVED it, it is certainly not the typical good old American beef stew with lean, dried out beef.  It is called Hungarian Beef Stew so I was not surprised it is different.  In fact when I ordered it the cashier specifically asked (warned?) if I don’t mind a little fat in the beef.  The texture of the beef is quite interesting – it has some lean parts, some tendons, and some fatty parts which made it a unique experience.  I guess I would be disappointed if all I get is something lean and dried out.  The carrots and potatoes were cooked just right.  The sauce was also very good, complex with sweet and savory the same time.  I would definitely order this again.  But I can see people can be disappointed if they are expecting the traditional beef stew with lean dry beef.  Definitely want to come back and try the other dishes they have.  Highly recommended!
The beef stew is not at all good it has a strong nasty after taste along with the rice. The presentation was ok but the food was awful... I would not recommend the beef stew.

Thx you for your response unfortunately your description on the menu doesn’t describe just tendon. I’m sure it may be good but not what the description of the menu described or pictures. Unfortunately a refund is not possible as I was in Hawaii for work at the time.
This spot is great! Delicious shrimp, tasty curry, hearty Hungarian stew... will definitely be back many times.

Saw a sign that said “Are you hungry?”. Walked through the court yard to EbiNomi, and ordered the Garlic Shrimp and Shrimp Cocktail. The Garlic Shrimp was AMAZING, the sauce is very flavorful and they remove the shells from the shrimp which is a small gesture, but improves the experience. The Cocktail de Camarones was also delicious. Went to Giovanni’s for the first time a few days after, after hearing raving reviews and I got to say that EbiNomi’s Garlic Shrimp is far superior. A MUST!

Tasty. A little more sauce would make them just as good at the North Shore food trucks, but the fact that the shrimp are already peeled evens it out. And although they normally have their to go items in plastic, they were able to serve mine in a paper box when I requested it. Mahalo
